# This file describes the installation of SpeciesGeoCoder on Mac OSX, GNU/Linux and Windows system.


===========================================
# Content of this file
1.) For the impatient
2.) Dependencies
3.) Installing on Mac OSX.
4.) Installing on Windows using Cygwin
5.) Installing the development version
===========================================

===
1.) For the impatient
	wget https://github.com/mtop/speciesgeocoder/archive/master.zip
	unzip master.zip
	cd speciesgeocoder-master/
	make
	make test # Not implemented yet
	sudo make install

===
2.) Dependencies*
Python module argparse (included in python v2.7) 
make
gcc

*The programs 'make' and 'gcc' are only needed if the pre-compiled 
versions of gdalinfo and gdallocationinfo does now work on your system. 
Both 'make' and 'gcc' should be installed on a regular GNU/Linux 
system. Mac OSX and Windows/Cygwin users can find installation 
instructions below.

===
3.) Installing on Mac OSX.
'make' and 'gcc' are part of the package 'Xcode' that is available on 
Appstore. After installation, open Xcode and go to: 
Preferences -> Downloads -> Components -> Command Line Tools, and 
install the commandline tools of Xcode.


### Installing using a web browser 
a). Direct your browser to the following URL (a compressed file will 
then be automatically downloaded):
https://github.com/mtop/speciesgeocoder/archive/master.zip

b). Unzip the file by clicking on it.
c). Open a terminal window and use the command "cd" and move into the 
	directory "speciesgeocoder-master/"
d). Type 'make distclean', 'make', 'make test' and 'sudo make install'
e). copy and paste the following command into your terminal window:
	./geocoder.py -l example_data/localities.csv -p example_data/polygons.txt -t example_data/*.tif

===
4.) Installing on Windows using Cygwin

### Installing using wget
### Copy and paste the following commands in a terminal
wget https://github.com/mtop/speciesgeocoder/archive/master.zip
unzip master.zip
cd speciesgeocoder-master/
make distclean
make 
make test # Not implemented yet
sudo (?) make install 


./geocoder.py -l example_data/localities.csv -p example_data/polygons.txt -t example_data/*.tif


5.) Installing the development version
### Copy and paste the following commands in a terminal
git clone git@github.com:mtop/speciesgeocoder.git
cd speciesgeocoder/
make distclean
make
make test
./geocoder.py -l example_data/localities.csv -p example_data/polygons.txt -t example_data/*.tif





